\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. cristata} (L.) Hyl.,{\i  Bot. Not. }{\b 1953}: 355 (1953) ({\i Koeleria phleoides} (Vill.) Pers.). Caespitose, with erect or geniculate, glabrous stems 5-60 cm. Leaves up to 18 cm × 8 mm; leaves and sheaths villous to pubescent, greenish when dry. Panicle 1-12 × 0·5-1(-2) cm, cylindrical and dense, or pyramidal, lax and more or less lobed. Pedicels scabridulous. Spikelets 3-7·5 mm. Glumes acute, pubescent or glabrous, the lower c. ¾ as long as the upper. Rhachilla-hairs not more than 0·5 mm. Lemma with 5 usually distinct veins, shortly 2-fid; awn 1-3 mm, arising near apex, usually straight. Anthers 0·2-0·5 mm. 2n = 26.{\i  Cultivated ground and dry, sandy grassland. Mediterranean region and S.W. Europe, extending northwards to} 47° 30' {\i N. in W. France and to E. Bulgaria.} Al Az Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Rs (K) Sa Si Tu.
