\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. hispida} (Savi) Jonsell, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  76}: 321 (1978) ({\i Koeleria hispida} (Savi) DC.,{\i  Festuca hispida} Savi). Stems 5-30 cm, more or less geniculate, glabrous. Leaves up to 10 cm × 7 mm, acuminate; leaves and sheaths more or less villous. Panicle 1-6 × 0·7-1·5 cm, ovoid, very dense. Pedicels smooth, very rigid. Spikelets 4-5 mm. Glumes acuminate, glabrous or ciliate on the keel, the lower c. ¾ as long as and much narrower than the upper. Rhachilla glabrous. Lemma with 5 prominent veins; awn of lower lemmas 3-5 mm, arising near apex, slightly curved. Anthers 0·7-1 mm.{\i  Mediterranean region, from Sardegna to W. Greece.} Gr It Sa Si.
